# --- Operating system junk ---
.DS_Store
._*
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# --- Editors ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# --- Node ---
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
package-lock.json

# --- Python helper scripts' leftovers ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- Release artifacts ---
# The release zip is attached to a GitHub Release, never committed to the repo.
*.zip

# --- Foundry compendium internals ---
# LOCK is created by a running Foundry and must never be committed.
# LOG / LOG.old are LevelDB's own diagnostic logs — not data, pure noise in diffs.
# Everything else in packs/ (*.ldb, *.log, CURRENT, MANIFEST-*) IS data. Do not ignore it.
packs/*/LOCK
packs/*/LOG
packs/*/LOG.old

# --- Maps ---
# Kept out of git on purpose. Large binary, and git history is permanent —
# release assets can be swapped freely, committed files cannot.
# The map still ships inside the release zip; this only keeps it out of history.
# If a map is ever created from scratch by a human and should live in the repo,
# add an exception below, e.g.:  !maps/harbour-hand-drawn.webp
maps/

# --- Local working folders (not part of the released system) ---
design/
oldVU/
maps/DE_*
